40|$|Section 5 of the Toxic Substances Control Act (TSCA) {{does not}} require any {{toxicity}} testing as a prerequisite for submission of a <b>Premanufacturing</b> <b>Notice</b> (PMN) for a new chemical. In order {{to compensate for the}} lack of actual test data, a process involving structure-activity relationships (SAR) for assessing hazard potential was constructed. The hazard assessment is then coupled with an estimation of potential exposure to determine potential risk. This process involves the use of multiple interdisciplinary teams that work within a 90 -day time frame to complete approximately 2000 risk assessments per year...|$|E

